sentences: Vinko Žganec (January 22, 1890 - December 12, 1976) was a Croatian ethnomusicologist.
He started to be interested in music early in his childhood and jotted down his first folk song in 1908.
In 1916, he published his first book of Croatian folk songs from Međimurje.
He studied theology and later law, becoming a Doctor of Law in 1919.
Music started to be his primary focus in 1945 when he became the head of the Ethnographic Museum in Zagreb.
